      • getFromTempMap

        java.lang.Object getFromTempMap(java.lang.Object key)
        Get the value corresponding to the given key. If the corresponding value is a KeyableBean it will be added to the bundle.
        Parameters:
        key - the key value to fetch
        Returns:
        the value for the given key

      • addToSessionMap

        void addToSessionMap(java.lang.Object key,
                   java.lang.Object value)
        Adds the key, value pair to the session map. Note that this does not add the object to the bundle. If you want it in the bundle, add it to the bundle and then add the resulting instance. For example: var user = find(u in User where xxx) context.SessionMarker.addToSessionMap(bundle.add(user))
        Parameters:
        key - key to map
        value - value to put in the map

      • getFromSessionMap

        java.lang.Object getFromSessionMap(java.lang.Object key)
        Get the value corresponding to the given key from the session map. This does nothing with the bundle, if you want the bean in the bundle add it explicitly, preferably before adding it to the session marker.
        Parameters:
        key - the key value to fetch
        Returns:
        the value for the given key
